ons about methodological approaches to understanding childhoods in context which is the focus of the concluding chapter. This is the third in a series of four books, written by experts in the field, which provides an introduction to childhood degree programmes and related modules. The series features international case studies, examples and readings to supplement the chapters, and is illustrated in full colour. Other books in the series are: · Understanding childhood: a cross-disciplinary approach · Children and young people's cultural worlds · Local childhoods, global issues  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChild rearingvCross-cultural studies. 0aChildrenvCross-cultural studies. 0aEducationvCross-cultural studies. 0aFamiliesvCross-cultural studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aClark, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Alison, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCrafter, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallacher, Lesley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammersley, Martyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehily, Mary Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraftl, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontgomery, Heather, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Dell, Lindsay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730581140uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447342915?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978144734291